<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-06T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-06T15:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860d.01/47: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-06T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            6, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>6247. Please ascertain the views of the Foreign Office with regard to
                                full recognition of Government of Finland.</p>
                            <p>It is considered desirable that if full recognition be accorded, it
                                be determined upon contemporaneously by the four principal
                                associated governments.</p>
                            <p>Repeat to Paris and Rome.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>